searches: </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Genetic Algorithm','','inherit','closed','closed','','195-autosave-v1','','','2024-03-05 10:18:48','2024-03-05 10:18:48','',195,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=282',0,'revision','',0),(283,1,'2024-03-05 10:19:08','2024-03-05 10:19:08','<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"full\",\"id\":196,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Genetic-Algorithm.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-196\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong><br>Introduction to Genetic Algorithms</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Genetic algorithms (GAs) are a class of optimization algorithms inspired by the principles of natural selection and genetics. They are designed to mimic the process of natural evolution to find solutions to complex optimization and search problems.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Historical Background</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The concept of genetic algorithms was first introduced by John Holland in the 1960s and further developed in the 1970s and 1980s. Holland, a computer scientist and psychologist, was interested in exploring how the principles of evolution could be applied to computational problem-solving. His seminal work, \"Adaptation in Natural and Artificial Systems,\" laid the foundation for genetic algorithms and evolutionary computation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Importance and Applications</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Genetic algorithms have gained prominence due to their ability to efficiently solve a wide range of optimization problems across various domains. Some key reasons for their importance include:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Robustness:</strong> Genetic algorithms can handle complex, nonlinear, and multi-modal optimization problems with numerous local optima.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Adaptability:</strong> They can adapt and evolve over generations, exploring diverse regions of the search space and converging towards optimal or near-optimal solutions.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Parallelism:</strong> Genetic algorithms inherently support parallel processing, making them suitable for distributed and parallel computing environments.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Versatility:</strong> Genetic algorithms can be applied to diverse applications such as:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Optimization problems in engineering, including structural design, scheduling, and parameter tuning.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Machine learning tasks like feature selection, neural network training, and hyperparameter optimization.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Robotics applications such as path planning, robot control, and evolutionary robotics.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Bioinformatics tasks like sequence alignment, protein folding, and gene expression analysis.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Design and creativity tasks like art generation, music composition, and game development.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In summary, genetic algorithms offer a powerful and flexible approach to optimization and problem-solving, making them a valuable tool across various fields and disciplines. Their ability to harness the principles of natural evolution enables them to tackle complex challenges that traditional optimization methods may struggle to address effectively.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Dig deeper into Genetic Algorithm </strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Course (text) <a href=\"https://www.tutorialspoint.com/genetic_algorithms\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://www.tutorialspoint.com/genetic_algorithms\"><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-green-cyan-color\">(tutorialspoint) genetic_algorithms</mark></a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Course (~ 6 hours) <mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-red-color\"> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLRqwX-V7Uu6bJM3VgzjNV5YxVxUwzALHV\">(youtube) 9.1: Genetic Algorithm: </a></mark></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Genetic Algorithm framework (for coding)</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Java MOEA framework: <a href=\"http://moeaframework.org/\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"http://moeaframework.org/\"><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-cyan-bluish-gray-color\">moeaframework.org</mark></a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Python PyGAD: <a href=\"https://pygad.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\"><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\">PyGAD - Python Genetic Algorithm!  PyGAD 3.3.1 documentation</mark></a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Genetic Algorithm Researches</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Student paper: <a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/student-papers/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"2\">Student Paper</a>s</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Prior Researches: <a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/prior-researches/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"248\">Prior Researches</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Genetic Algorithm','','inherit','closed','closed','','195-revision-v1','','','2024-03-05 10:19:08','2024-03-05 10:19:08','',195,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=283',0,'revision','',0),(284,1,'2024-03-05 10:21:14','2024-03-05 10:21:14','','FIT','','inherit','open','closed','','fit-2','','','2024-03-05 10:21:14','2024-03-05 10:21:14','',271,'http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/FIT.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(285,1,'2024-03-05 10:22:14','2024-03-05 10:22:14','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>header content for: Problem of Gale Shapley header content for: Problem of Gale Shapley header content for: Problem of Gale Shapley header content for: Problem of Gale Shapley header content for: Problem of Gale Shapley header content for: Problem of Gale Shapley</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:file {\"id\":95,\"href\":\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Problem_of_GaleShapley.pdf\",\"displayPreview\":true} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-file\"><object class=\"wp-block-file__embed\" data=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Problem_of_GaleShapley.pdf\" type=\"application/pdf\" style=\"width:100%;height:600px\" aria-label=\"Problem_of_GaleShapley\"></object><a id=\"wp-block-file--media-05f41221-b2f6-4ea7-aaab-15c3f5ba4535\" href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/2024/02/25/problem-of-gale-shapley/problem_of_galeshapley/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Problem_of_GaleShapley</a><a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Problem_of_GaleShapley.pdf\" class=\"wp-block-file__button wp-element-button\" download aria-describedby=\"wp-block-file--media-05f41221-b2f6-4ea7-aaab-15c3f5ba4535\">Download</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:file -->','Problem of Gale Shapley','','inherit','closed','closed','','94-revision-v1','','','2024-03-05 10:22:14','2024-03-05 10:22:14','',94,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=285',0,'revision','',0),(286,1,'2024-03-05 10:26:37','2024-03-05 10:26:37','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hanyu Gu, Hue Chi Lam , Yakov Zinder<br>School of Mathematical and Physical Sciences, University of Technology Sydney,<br>PO Box 123, Broadway, NSW 2007, Australia</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Abstract</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">This study addresses the scheduling problem where every job requires several types of resources. At every point in time, the capacity of resources is limited. When necessary, the capacity can be increased at a cost. Each job has a due date, and the processing times of jobs are random variables with a known probability distribution. The considered problem is to determine a schedule that minimises the total cost, which consists of the cost incurred due to the violation of resource limits and the total tardiness of jobs. A genetic algorithm enhanced by local search is proposed. The sample average approximation method is used to construct a confidence interval for the optimality gap of the obtained solutions. Computational study on the application of the sample average approximation method and genetic algorithm is presented. It is revealed that the proposed method is capable of providing high-quality solutions to large instances in a reasonable time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:file {\"id\":277,\"href\":\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A-hybrid-genetic-algorithm-for-scheduling-jobs-s_2022_EURO-Journal-on-Comput.pdf\",\"displayPreview\":true} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-file\"><object class=\"wp-block-file__embed\" data=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A-hybrid-genetic-algorithm-for-scheduling-jobs-s_2022_EURO-Journal-on-Comput.pdf\" type=\"application/pdf\" style=\"width:100%;height:600px\" aria-label=\"A-hybrid-genetic-algorithm-for-scheduling-jobs-s_2022_EURO-Journal-on-Comput\"></object><a id=\"wp-block-file--media-27f9beac-ebee-4fe7-be08-41360a06613c\" href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A-hybrid-genetic-algorithm-for-scheduling-jobs-s_2022_EURO-Journal-on-Comput.pdf\">A-hybrid-genetic-algorithm-for-scheduling-jobs-s_2022_EURO-Journal-on-Comput</a><a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A-hybrid-genetic-algorithm-for-scheduling-jobs-s_2022_EURO-Journal-on-Comput.pdf\" class=\"wp-block-file__button wp-element-button\" download aria-describedby=\"wp-block-file--media-27f9beac-ebee-4fe7-be08-41360a06613c\">Download</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:file -->','A hybrid genetic algorithm for scheduling jobssharing multiple resources under uncertainty','','publish','open','open','','a-hybrid-genetic-algorithm-for-scheduling-jobssharing-multiple-resources-under-uncertainty','','','2024-03-05 11:51:32','2024-03-05 11:51:32','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=286',0,'post','',0),(287,1,'2024-03-05 10:26:37','2024-03-05 10:26:37','<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">This study addresses the scheduling problem where every job<br>requires several types of resources. At every point in time, the<br>capacity of resources is limited. When necessary, the capacity<br>can be increased at a cost. Each job has a due date, and<br>the processing times of jobs are random variables with 